{"id":"el-3y1","type":"document","createdAt":"2026-03-11T11:49:32.170Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T15:28:52.679Z","createdBy":"el-0000","tags":[],"metadata":{"purpose":"slack-integration-context"},"title":"Slack App Integration - Architecture Context","contentType":"markdown","content":"# Slack App Integration - Architecture Context\n\n## Module & Package Structure\n\nModule: `checker` (go.mod)\nAll application code lives under `internal/`:\n\n```\ncmd/app/main.go              - Entry point\ninternal/config/config.go    - YAML config + env overrides\ninternal/db/repository.go    - Repository interface\ninternal/db/postgres.go      - PostgreSQL implementation\ninternal/scheduler/           - Scheduler, worker pool, factories\ninternal/slack/client.go     - SlackClient (slack-go/slack)\ninternal/slack/blocks.go     - Block Kit builders\ninternal/slack/models.go     - CheckAlertInfo, emoji helpers\ninternal/web/server.go       - Gin web server\ninternal/web/slack_handlers.go - Interactive button handlers\ninternal/models/slack.go     - SlackAlertThread, AlertSilence\nmigrations/                  - golang-migrate SQL files\n```\n\n## What's Already Done (on master)\n\n1. **go.mod**: `slack-go/slack` dependency added\n2. **Config**: `SlackApp` struct with BotToken, SigningSecret, DefaultChannel + env var overrides (SLACK_BOT_TOKEN, SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET, SLACK_DEFAULT_CHANNEL)\n3. **Repository interface**: 6 Slack methods declared (CreateSlackThread, GetUnresolvedThread, ResolveThread, UpdateSlackThread, CreateSilence, IsCheckSilenced)\n4. **Scheduler wiring**: `SlackAlerter` parameter threaded through RunScheduler → NewScheduler → NewWorkerPool → executeCheck. State transition detection in executeCheck (wasUnhealthy logic).\n5. **Web server**: `/api/slack/interactive` endpoint registered, accepts `*slack.SlackClient`\n6. **Slack handlers**: imports fixed to `checker/internal/...`, uses logrus\n7. **Main.go**: SlackClient + SlackAlerter initialization, passed to scheduler and web server\n\n## What's NOT Done Yet (gaps to fill)\n\n1. **Migration 000003**: Need `slack_alert_threads` table\n2. **PostgreSQL methods**: 6 methods declared in interface but NOT implemented in postgres.go\n3. **SlackAlerter struct**: Referenced by scheduler but the actual struct + methods don't exist yet in `internal/scheduler/slack_alerts.go`\n4. **Dead code cleanup**: Old files using `my/checker` imports still exist: `slack/interactions.go`, `scheduler/slack_alerts.go`, `alerts/slack_app.go`\n\n## Key Types\n\n```go\n// models.SlackAlertThread\ntype SlackAlertThread struct {\n    ID, CheckUUID, ChannelID, ThreadTs, ParentTs string\n    IsResolved bool; CreatedAt time.Time; ResolvedAt *time.Time\n}\n\n// models.AlertSilence\ntype AlertSilence struct {\n    ID int; Scope, Target, SilencedBy string\n    SilencedAt time.Time; ExpiresAt *time.Time\n    Reason string; Active bool\n}\n\n// slack.CheckAlertInfo\ntype CheckAlertInfo struct {\n    UUID, Name, Project, Group, CheckType, Frequency, Message string\n    IsHealthy bool; Severity string\n}\n\n// models.CheckDefinition - fields relevant to Slack:\n// UUID, Name, Project, GroupName, Type, Duration, IsHealthy, Config\n```\n\n## Repository Methods Needed\n\n```go\n// Thread management\nCreateSlackThread(ctx, checkUUID, channelID, threadTs, parentTs string) error\nGetUnresolvedThread(ctx, checkUUID string) (models.SlackAlertThread, error)\nResolveThread(ctx, checkUUID string) error\nUpdateSlackThread(ctx, checkUUID, threadTs, channelID string) error\n\n// Silence management\nCreateSilence(ctx, silence models.AlertSilence) error\nIsCheckSilenced(ctx, checkUUID, project string) (bool, error)\nDeactivateSilence(ctx context.Context, scope, target string) error\nGetActiveSilences(ctx context.Context) ([]models.AlertSilence, error)\n\n// Query helpers (for slash commands)\nGetUnhealthyChecks(ctx context.Context) ([]models.CheckDefinition, error)\n```\n\n## Existing DB Schema (migration 000002)\n\n```sql\n-- On check_definitions table:\nALTER TABLE check_definitions ADD COLUMN slack_thread_ts TEXT;\nALTER TABLE check_definitions ADD COLUMN slack_channel_id TEXT;\n\n-- Separate table:\nCREATE TABLE alert_silences (\n    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    scope TEXT NOT NULL,\n    target TEXT NOT NULL,\n    silenced_by TEXT,\n    silenced_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),\n    expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\n    reason TEXT,\n    active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true\n);\nCREATE INDEX idx_alert_silences_active ON alert_silences(active, scope, target);\n```\n","version":2,"previousVersionId":"el-3y1","category":"reference","status":"active","immutable":false}
{"id":"el-5tm","type":"document","createdAt":"2026-03-11T15:28:17.063Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T15:28:17.063Z","createdBy":"el-0000","tags":[],"metadata":{},"contentType":"markdown","content":"The architecture doc el-3y1 (Slack App Integration - Architecture Context) is missing several repository methods from its 'Repository Methods Needed' section. Add the following methods that exist on master:\n\n- DeactivateSilence(ctx context.Context, scope, target string) error — deactivates active silences by scope/target (was already on master before el-5fre)\n- GetActiveSilences(ctx context.Context) ([]models.AlertSilence, error) — returns all active, non-expired silences (added in el-5fre for slash commands)\n- GetUnhealthyChecks(ctx context.Context) ([]models.CheckDefinition, error) — returns unhealthy enabled checks (added in el-5fre for slash commands)\n\nThese should be added alongside the existing documented methods: CreateSlackThread, GetUnresolvedThread, ResolveThread, UpdateSlackThread, CreateSilence, IsCheckSilenced.","version":1,"previousVersionId":null,"category":"other","status":"active","immutable":false}
